    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT355-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">iravukkuṟi vanta talaimakaṟkut tōḻi nērntu kūṟiyatu. </p>


        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Spoken in pain by the confidante to HIM, who came to the
          night tryst. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT355">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> peyalkaṇ maṟaittaliṉ vicumpukā ṇalaiyē</l>
          <l> nīrparan toḻukali ṉilaṅkā ṇalaiyē</l>
          <l> yellai cēṟali ṉiruḷperitu paṭṭaṉṟu</l>
          <l> pallōr tuñcum pāṉāṭ kaṅkul</l>
          <l> yāṅkuvan taṉaiyō vōṅkal veṟpa</l>
          <l> vēṅkai kamaḻumeñ ciṟukuṭi</l>
          <l> yāṅkaṟin taṉaiyō nōkō yāṉē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>As rain shrouded [your] eyes, you didn't see the sky.</l>
          <l>As the water spread [and] flowed, you didn't see the ground.</l>
          <l>As daylight went, a great darkness fell. </l>
          <l rend="indent2">While many are sleeping, at midnight</l>
          <l>how did you come, man from the high mountains?</l>
          <l rend="indent">[The way to] our little home smelling of Vēṅkai,</l>
          <l>how did you know? Ah, I ache.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
